HEADWORD: Tombstone
<hw>Tomb"stone`</hw> <pr>(t⟦oomac⟧m"st⟦omac⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A stone or small stone monument erected over a grave, bearing the
name of the dead person interred there, to preserve the memory of the
deceased.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tomcat</ent>⟦br⟧
